Extended Data Fig. 9 | Histopathological feature representations before and after retraining of Inception-V4. UMAP representation of the
histopathological features from the original Inception model (n=200 tiles randomly selected for each tissue type/JPEG quality) (a, b) and the modified,
retrained architecture (e, d). a, lung adenocarcinoma, squamous cell carcinoma and normal lung tissue highlighted. b, breast tumor and normal from TCGA
and breast tumor from METABRIC highlighted. ¢, as ina, but for the modified architecture. d, as ¢ based on the modified architecture. In each figure, the
plot on the right side is colored by tissue type and the plot on the left side is colored by jpeg quality.
